
                                                        +-------+
                                                        |  .OJ  |
                                                        +-------+

OUT JUSTIFY  aligns the specified number  of input text  lines to
the outside of the page (the side opposite from the side on which
it is bound).

     +-------+---------------------------------------------+
     |       |                                             |
     |  .OJ  |    <<.U+>1<.U->|n|ON|OFF|line>                        |<.NORMAL>
     |       |                                             |
     +-------+---------------------------------------------+

This control word causes a break.    It performs like Left Adjust
(.LA) on even-numbered pages and like Right Adjust (.RI)  on odd-
numbered pages.   The operands and other considerations are iden-
tical to those for the CENTER control word;  see the .CE descrip-
tion for details.

